<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="64" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,158,184]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1973" box="[320,578,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regis-jubae">
<emphasis box="[320,578,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Callitriche regis-jubae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Mediterranean, where it is known from Extremadura and Andalucia in the Iberian Peninsula, 
<collectingCountry box="[548,652,195,221]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[665,751,194,220]" name="Tunisia" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[814,865,194,220]" name="Italy" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fennane, M. &amp; Ibn Tattou, M. &amp; Ouyahya, A. &amp; El Oualidi, J." box="[882,1114,194,221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" refId="ref14699" refString="Fennane, M., Ibn Tattou, M., Ouyahya, A. &amp; El Oualidi, J. (2007) Flore pratique du Maroc: manuel de determination des plantes vasculaires: Angiospermae (Leguminosae - Lentibulariaceae), Vol. 2. Rabat Institut Scientifique, Rabat, 636 pp." type="book" year="2007">
Fennane 
<emphasis box="[987,1039,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghrabi-Gammar, Z. &amp; Daoud-Bouattour, A. &amp; Ferchichi, H. &amp; Gammar, A. M. &amp; Muller, S. D. &amp; Rhazi, L. &amp; Ben Saad-Limam, S." box="[1127,1447,194,221]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" pagination="19 - 40" refId="ref14918" refString="Ghrabi-Gammar, Z., Daoud-Bouattour, A., Ferchichi, H., Gammar, A. M., Muller, S. D., Rhazi, L. &amp; Ben Saad-Limam, S. (2009) Flore vasculaire rare, endemique et menacee des zones humides de Tunisie. Revue d Ecologie (Terre et Vie) 64: 19 - 40." type="journal article" year="2009">
Ghrabi-Gammar 
<emphasis box="[1321,1372,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Prancl, J. &amp; Fehrer, J. &amp; Caklova, P. &amp; Bambasova, V. &amp; Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z." box="[136,338,230,257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" pagination="1016 - 1041" refId="ref16234" refString="Prancl, J., Fehrer, J., Caklova, P., Bambasova, V., Lucanova, M. &amp; Kaplan, Z. (2020) Intricate evolutionary history of Callitriche (Plantaginaceae) taxa elucidated by a combination of DNA sequencing and genome size. Taxon 69 (5): 1016 - 1041. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / tax. 12315" type="journal article" year="2020">
Prančl 
<emphasis box="[214,263,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). There is also a fairly poor specimen from Tenerife (K) that could be this species, but is inadequate for formal confirmation. In 
<collectingCountry box="[459,560,267,293]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Morocco</collectingCountry>
it is frequent along the coast from Casablanca northwards, as well as in the Central Plateau (
<figureCitation box="[323,412,302,328]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,191,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1435,190,1951]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Known distribution of Callitriche species in Morocco. A. C. obtusangula. B. C. regis-jubae. C. C. stagnalis. D. C. truncata subsp. occidentalis. E. C. truncata subsp. truncata. F. All records of all Callitriche species in Morocco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875725/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Elevation in 
<collectingCountry box="[575,681,303,329]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Morocco</collectingCountry>
: 
<quantity box="[691,805,302,329]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" metricValueMax="11.6" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" unit="m" value="580.0" valueMax="1160.0" valueMin="0.0">0–1160 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,1373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,436,338,364]" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1973" box="[464,719,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regis-jubae">
<emphasis box="[464,719,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Callitriche regis-jubae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically occurs in seasonal wetlands, as well as in seasonal pools in the channel of rivers, and ditches in inundated pasture. In 
<collectingCountry box="[815,916,375,401]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Morocco</collectingCountry>
it has been recorded from wet flushes, streams, cupular pools in granite, marshes, and seasonal pools. It was recorded with a wide range of species, of which 19% may be considered truly aquatic, 52% characteristic of seasonal wetlands, and 29% terrestrial, reflecting its association with seasonal wetlands. Typical associates include 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prancl" baseAuthorityName="Warburg &amp; Eig" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[733,1137,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="brutia" subSpecies="naftolskyi">
<emphasis box="[733,934,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Callitriche brutia</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[1028,1137,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">naftolskyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1156,1444,482,509]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1976" box="[1156,1291,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mathezii">C. mathezii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[1306,1444,482,509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">C. stagnalis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roth" authorityYear="1827" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[136,345,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Crassula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaillantii">
<emphasis box="[136,345,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Crassula vaillantii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gussone" authorityYear="1826" box="[358,573,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Elatinaceae" genus="Elatine" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macropoda">
<emphasis box="[358,573,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Elatine macropoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roemer &amp; Schultes" authorityYear="1817" box="[585,811,518,544]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Eleocharis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="11" pageNumber="64" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis box="[585,811,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="64">Eleocharis palustris</emphasis>
